<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>They recently revealed the band was reuniting and releasing a comeback album.</p>

<p>And Faye Tozer looked sensational as she headed to The One Show in London on Friday night to perform Steps' comeback single What The Future Holds.</p>

<p>The singer, 44, was joined by bandmate Lisa Scott-Lee ahead of the show with both women putting on a stylish display in purple mini dresses as they left their hotel.</p>

<p>Looking good: Faye Tozer flaunted her toned figure in a purple mini dress as she left her hotel and headed to The One Show in London on Friday</p>

<p>Faye flaunted her toned figure in a satin mini dress which boasted a pretty floral pattern all over it.</p>

<p>Her frock also featured stylish puffed-sleeves and a high-neck line, with the star completing her ensemble with some white trainers.  </p>

<p>The blonde beauty tied her hair back into a sleek ponytail ahead of the show but was later seen with her locks flowing over her shoulders.</p>

<p>While Lisa, 44, also cut a fashionable figure as she left the hotel, wearing a chic purple dress with long sleeves and a ruched detail at the waist.</p>

<p>Glam: Bandmate Lisa Scott-Lee also cut a stylish figure in a purple long-sleeved dress and black heels</p>

<p>'The fab five!': Lisa shared a selfie taken by H to her Instagram after the band performed their new song and expressed her excitement at being back together</p>

<p>She added some extra height to her frame with a pair of black stiletto heels with a peep-toe detail.</p>

<p>The brunette styled her hair in curls and let them cascade over her shoulders as she strutted to the taxi waiting to whisk her off to the TV studios.</p>

<p>Although not seen leaving the hotel, the pair's bandmates Claire Richards, Ian 'H' Watkins and Lee Latchford-Evan joined them at The One Show.</p>

<p>After debuting the new song, Lisa took to Instagram to share her excitement about the band being back together and making music again.</p>

<p>Stunning: The singer wore her brunette locks down and curled ahead of the TV performance</p>

<p>Work it: Lisa appeared to be in good spirits as she went to meet her fellow bandmates </p>

<p>Writing in the caption to a selfie taken by H, she wrote: 'Here’s the fab 5!! Thanks to everyone for tuning in and thanks to <?php echo e('@'); ?>alexjonesthomson <?php echo e('@'); ?>riyadhk and the <?php echo e('@'); ?>bbc team for keeping us safe!'</p>

<p>Steps delighted fans last Monday when they announced they were reunited for a new album and nationwide tour in 2021.   </p>

<p>The group first announced the venture with a series of cryptic posts spelling out their iconic name, before confirming rumours they're set to join forces once again for a new album.</p>

<p>All smiles: Lisa and Faye were joined by Claire, H and Lee at the studios where they performed new single What The Future Holds</p>

<p>Wow! Lisa also looked sensational in her stage outfit, which included a corset style top and a pair of statement sparkly shoes</p>

<p>They also eased that their latest tour would be their 'biggest spectacle yet' as they join forces with stars including Sia to pen singles for the album.</p>

<p>The band first teased their new music by each tweeting an illuminated letter, which when put together spelled out their name.   </p>

<p>One post read 'One foot in the past...' as another completed '...one foot in the future', before another added: 'Tell me what the future holds Crystal ball.'</p>

<p>After their respective posts a snap showed the members together, as they confirmed their album would be released in late November.</p>

<p>Back together! Steps (L-R Claire Richards, Lee Hatchford-Evans, Lisa Scott-Lee, Ian 'H' Watkins and Faye Tozer) have announced they're reuniting for a new album and nationwide tour in 2021</p>

<p>The caption said: 'We couldn't keep it a secret any longer!! </p>

<p>'Our new album What The Future Holds arrives on November 27th, and it's available to pre-order from 8am tomorrow!'</p>

<p>The band went onto gush that they couldn't wait to go back on the road for their tour.</p>

<p>They said: 'We will never forget the past with Steps, it's what made us, but we've got to look to the future too. We were so thrilled that the last album was a success and it gave us a new lease of life. </p>

<p>Comeback: The band premiered their new single on BBC Radio 2, with their tour set to take place later in 2021</p>

<p>Funky: Steps celebrated their comeback by releasing the video for their new single What The Future Holds on Friday</p>

<p>'Performing live has always been our favourite part of being in Steps – we had the most fun of our career on the last tour and we're already planning for the next one to be our biggest spectacle yet.  </p>

<p>'We're also thrilled to have Sophie Ellis-Bextor as our special guest on the What The Future Holds 2021 Tour – her catalogue is full of floor-fillers and she knows how to get any party started. </p>

<p>'We are so excited for everyone to hear this new album and to come join us on tour.'</p>

<p>Since then Steps have announced their comeback single and shared the video to the catchy tune, What The Future Holds.  </p>

<p>And in a special nod to the past, the beloved pop group brought back their iconic hand moves for the futuristic video which sees them travel to an illuminated city.</p>

<p>Stars: Steps split in 2001 after fourteen consecutive top 5 singles, sold over 20 million records and reached Number One with three albums and three singles (pictured in 1998)</p>
